<br>
You can also use those baking bags you can get in the grocery store.  I think they're called Brownin' Bags or some such thing.  I've used them before, and they work pretty well, too.<br>
<br>
Whichever method I use, I usually take some onion garlic and put pieces of it up under the skin in various places and some inside the bird as well.  Salt and pepper and any other herbs you like on the outside after rubbing it with butter.  Makes a great chicken and/or turkey. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Maritzia Tinkerboltz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
