<br>
Then we cut up the carcass and boil it for broth with some onions and a bit of garlic (not too much since you'll want to spice the broth for whatever you are making with it).  We let it boil pretty far down so the broth is really rich, and so it doesn't take up too much space in the freezer.  Then we seperate it into glad bowls and put it in the freezer.  We use it to make soups, chicken and dumplings (with some of the above mentioned chicken), rice (make it with half chicken broth, half water for a really tasty side dish), or anything else that calls for chicken broth.  Cheaper and tastier than the canned stuff. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Maritzia Tinkerboltz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
